Even though Khalil is happily married, Victoria struggles throughout this romantic comedy to hold back her feelings for him.

link.synopsis: Yeardley Smith stars in this wry comedy about three couples at various pit stops on the rocky road to romance, beginning with Caitlin (Smith), who tells her longtime boyfriend, Jonah (Adam Carl), that it's time to tie the knot. One evening, Caitlin and Jonah stew over their dilemma while entertaining Jonah's sister, Zellie (Zibby Allen); her new beau, ex-con Jude (Patrick Day); and their friend Bart (Richie Keen), whose marriage is dissolving.

link.synopsis: Director Chun-Chun Wong mixes documentary and fiction, comedy and drama in this engaging film about the power of first love. When aimless Joe (Jaycee Chan) is dumped by his mercurial girlfriend, Flora (Fiona Sit), he finds an unusual way to win her back: a magical website. The Break Up Club site promises to bring Flora back to Joe if he causes another couple to split, and he's thrilled when it works. But what happens when Flora drops him again?

link.synopsis: This bleak comedy set in Istanbul centers on despondent widower Adnan (Reha Özcan), who stumbles from one low-level job to the next in a malaise of grief and misfortune, while teenage son Burak (Kamer Celenk) edges ever closer to delinquent disaster right beneath his nose. The relatives are sympathetic but all out of patience, and the city beyond is coldly indifferent; sink or swim, father and son are each other's only chance for survival.
link.title: synopsis
Turn Left at the End of the World

link.synopsis: In an attempt to rake in fast cash, con man Marty Holland (Hal March) stages a beauty contest for which a winner -- a gangster's girlfriend (Jean Willes) -- has already been chosen. But when one of the other contestants (Merry Anders) catches his eye, he'd much rather give her the crown. During the filming of this black-and-white comedy, leading man March was seen every Tuesday on TV as host of the game show "The $64,000 Question."
link.title: synopsis
The Ealing Comedy Collection: Whisky Galore

link.synopsis: In this offbeat comedy, hired gun Ray Shoesmith (Scott Ryan) learns that his neighbor, Max Totti (Massimiliano Andrighetto), is an aspiring filmmaker, and he soon agrees to be the subject of Max's all-access documentary about life in the Melbourne underworld. The charismatic Ray proves surprisingly chatty, engaging the director in discussions of his past, his work and his pop-cultural leanings while ruthlessly expediting his deadly assignments.
link.title: synopsis

link.synopsis: This engaging comedy is set in Finnish Lapland, where unemployed Janne (Jussi Vatanen) wastes time with his slacker pals, much to the annoyance of his girlfriend, Inari (Pamela Tola). After he fails to buy a cable box, she gives him until the morning to find one ... or else. Along with his eccentric and depressed chums, Janne hits on a wild scheme to provide independent taxi service, but as complications pile up, he's forced to act more maturely.
link.title: synopsis
The Monastery: Mr. Vig and the Nun

link.synopsis: Don Worley stars as the title character in this comedy based on his popular Web series. Mr. Shepherd makes a modest living selling freeze-dried pets, but it's not enough to support his mom's (Diane Hruska) vices: prescription drugs and donations to televangelists. Things look dire when Shepherd loses his job ... until he decides to answer a higher calling. Tough guy Danny Trejo co-stars as Shepherd's jovial neighbor.

link.synopsis: Longing to become more worldly, virginal Irish farmer Donal (Domhnall Gleeson) hires immigrant prostitute Kim (Luanne Gordon) to introduce him to sex, and soon the two become lovers. Before long, they're also business partners running their own escort service. But Donal's newfound self-assurance backfires when he tries to pursue his longtime crush on local lovely Melanie (Kelly Campbell). Screenwriter Tom Hall also directs this dark comedy.

Unpracticed in romance but now determined to take charge of his fate, he begins to woo university professor Paola (Paola Venditto), whom he spied in the theater one day. Federico Veiroj helms this charming romantic comedy.
